855
00:55:10,675 --> 00:55:12,759
They were never harmed in any way.

856
00:55:13,094 --> 00:55:14,678
He's fucking lying!
They beat the shite out of us!

857
00:55:18,308 --> 00:55:20,142
Silence! Stop this noise!

858
00:55:21,686 --> 00:55:23,729
Please believe us!
They beat us!

859
00:55:24,147 --> 00:55:25,856
Silence!
Just be quiet.

860
00:55:25,940 --> 00:55:27,774
Sit them down!

861
00:55:28,276 --> 00:55:29,776
Silence in the court!

862
00:55:32,906 --> 00:55:34,573
Mr. Conlon says

863
00:55:35,658 --> 00:55:38,619
that you pulled him by the hair
and squeezed his testicles.

864
00:55:39,871 --> 00:55:41,371
I never even spoke
to Mr. Conlon.

865
00:55:41,873 --> 00:55:43,457
I hope you burn in hell, Dixon.

866
00:55:43,958 --> 00:55:45,000
Silence!

867
00:55:45,084 --> 00:55:49,463
Mr. Hill says the police sat astride
him and put a gun in his mouth.

868
00:55:51,132 --> 00:55:53,217
There was no pressure of any kind.

869
00:55:53,593 --> 00:55:56,386
You can go and fuck yourself,
you lying fucking bastard!

870
00:55:56,471 --> 00:55:58,472
Order! Order in court!

871
00:55:58,556 --> 00:56:01,141
Inspector, in the case
of the four main defendants,

872
00:56:01,226 --> 00:56:03,268
you have no corroborating
evidence of any kind.

873
00:56:03,853 --> 00:56:06,647
I have the confessions of four obvious terrorists.
What more do you want?

874
00:56:07,065 --> 00:56:10,234
Well, nitroglycerine
is a highly toxic substance.

875
00:56:10,526 --> 00:56:12,236
It's when the substance
to be tested...

876
00:56:12,320 --> 00:56:15,614
After a few weeks, we were
bored out of our minds.

877
00:56:16,032 --> 00:56:18,450
Just messed around and that there.

878
00:56:18,743 --> 00:56:21,328
They must've been
desperate for evidence.

879
00:56:21,412 --> 00:56:23,121
They produced my Auntie
Annie's washing-up gloves

880
00:56:23,206 --> 00:56:25,707
like a rabbit out of a hat
at one point.

881
00:56:26,084 --> 00:56:28,293
Then it was my turn to take the stand.

882
00:56:28,378 --> 00:56:31,713
Mr. Conlon,
did you bomb Guildford?

883
00:56:32,674 --> 00:56:34,174
No, I didn't.

884
00:56:35,385 --> 00:56:37,761
The police claim that you were in
Guildford on the night of the bombing.

885
00:56:37,845 --> 00:56:39,638
Can you tell us where you were?

886
00:56:40,181 --> 00:56:42,557
I was in a park in London
at that time.

887
00:56:42,642 --> 00:56:43,892
Who with?

888
00:56:43,977 --> 00:56:45,602
With Paul Hill sitting there.

889
00:56:46,854 --> 00:56:49,147
You met somebody else that
night, about 8:00 p.m.

890
00:56:49,691 --> 00:56:52,401
Aye, I met a man called Charlie Burke.

891
00:56:52,485 --> 00:56:53,819
And who is he?

892
00:56:53,903 --> 00:56:56,363
He was just like a,
you know, like a fellow,

893
00:56:56,447 --> 00:56:58,156
a homeless guy
that we met in the park.

894
00:56:58,866 --> 00:57:00,492
Why do you remember
this man so clearly?

895
00:57:01,703 --> 00:57:04,121
I remember thinking that if I
didn't get out of London fast,

896
00:57:04,205 --> 00:57:05,539
I was gonna end up like him.

897
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:08,959
You told this to the police?
Aye.

898
00:57:09,043 --> 00:57:10,168
What did they say?

899
00:57:10,253 --> 00:57:11,712
They said he didn't exist.

900
00:57:12,922 --> 00:57:16,508
Mr. Conlon, why did you confess
to the Guildford bombing?

901
00:57:18,136 --> 00:57:19,678
They beat me

902
00:57:20,888 --> 00:57:22,764
and then they threatened
to kill my father.

903
00:57:23,141 --> 00:57:25,267
Will you repeat that please?

904
00:57:25,351 --> 00:57:27,477
They terrorized me for seven days.

905
00:57:27,937 --> 00:57:30,230
And after that, they
threatened to kill my father.

906
00:57:30,315 --> 00:57:32,649
I'd have fucking signed
anything after that.

907
00:57:34,068 --> 00:57:35,110
Excuse my language.

908
00:57:35,194 --> 00:57:36,194
Thank you.

909
00:57:38,573 --> 00:57:42,242
You expect this jury to believe
that decorated police officers

910
00:57:42,618 --> 00:57:45,662
would risk their career
and their reputation

911
00:57:45,747 --> 00:57:47,873
by threatening your father?

912
00:57:47,999 --> 00:57:50,667
I don't expect them to believe it
by the time you finish with them,

913
00:57:50,752 --> 00:57:52,586
but it happens to be truth, you know.

914
00:57:53,046 --> 00:57:54,921
You're an honest man,
aren't you, Mr. Conlon?

915
00:57:56,215 --> 00:57:57,424
I like to think so.

916
00:57:58,509 --> 00:58:01,762
You've told us you remember
this Charlie Burke very well.

917
00:58:02,722 --> 00:58:03,764
Aye.

918
00:58:04,432 --> 00:58:08,185
Do you remember telling the police
anything else about that night?

919
00:58:09,604 --> 00:58:10,896
Let me refresh your memory.

920
00:58:10,980 --> 00:58:12,356
You told Inspector Dixon

921
00:58:12,732 --> 00:58:14,983
that you had committed
a robbery on that night.

922
00:58:16,110 --> 00:58:17,861
Now do you remember?

923
00:58:20,198 --> 00:58:21,281
Aye.

924
00:58:21,949 --> 00:58:23,575
Who did you rob?

925
00:58:25,328 --> 00:58:26,495
Robbed a hooker.

926
00:58:27,121 --> 00:58:28,205
You robbed a prostitute?

927
00:58:28,289 --> 00:58:29,414
Aye.

928
00:58:30,166 --> 00:58:31,875
And we are expected to believe a man

929
00:58:31,959 --> 00:58:34,044
who claims he stole from a prostitute

930
00:58:34,128 --> 00:58:36,713
before we would
believe 10 police officers

931
00:58:36,798 --> 00:58:39,674
who stood here on oath
and called you a liar?

932
00:58:40,301 --> 00:58:42,010
It's the truth.

933
00:58:42,095 --> 00:58:43,428
You know, I mean...

934
00:58:44,389 --> 00:58:46,932
I'm bound to say I don't
find you very convincing.

935
00:58:47,433 --> 00:58:49,017
Thank you, Mr. Conlon.

936
00:58:53,564 --> 00:58:57,150
Why didn't you tell me that
you stole from that woman?

937
00:58:58,820 --> 00:59:02,155
You should've called me.
I would've sent the money.

938
00:59:08,496 --> 00:59:11,665
Are you gonna be a thief
and a liar all your life?

939
00:59:13,543 --> 00:59:17,129
Standing up in that witness box,
making faces to your mates.

940
00:59:30,309 --> 00:59:33,437
At least you told the truth in there.
That'll stand you.

941
00:59:39,986 --> 00:59:42,571
Are you not going to eat that sausage?

942
00:59:43,573 --> 00:59:44,698
No.

943
00:59:46,868 --> 00:59:48,952
They put a gun in my mouth

944
00:59:49,370 --> 00:59:52,497
and made me confess to a
murder I didn't commit.

945
00:59:53,791 --> 00:59:56,084
So I said I did the big bombing

946
00:59:56,544 --> 00:59:59,671
and named anybody I knew
who was not in the IRA.

947
01:00:00,047 --> 01:00:02,048
Not in the IRA?

948
01:00:02,133 --> 01:00:03,717
Definitely not in the IRA.

949
01:00:04,177 --> 01:00:05,177
Why?

950
01:00:06,554 --> 01:00:08,013
You know why.

951
01:00:12,810 --> 01:00:15,562
Well, I just wanted to show
how ridiculous it all was.

952
01:00:16,063 --> 01:00:19,608
Inspector, the defendant
Conlon presented an alibi.

953
01:00:19,984 --> 01:00:21,359
One Charlie Burke.

954
01:00:21,444 --> 01:00:23,904
Yes, sir, that name did appear in Mr.
Conlon's statement.

955
01:00:23,988 --> 01:00:25,489
We investigated it.

956
01:00:25,573 --> 01:00:27,240
We couldn't find any trace
of such a person.

957
01:00:27,950 --> 01:00:30,785
And then there was this question
of the robbery of a prostitute.

958
01:00:31,245 --> 01:00:33,830
No robberies were reported
in that area that night.

959
01:00:33,915 --> 01:00:37,709
At the start of this trial,
I shook Gerry Conlon's hand.

960
01:00:39,086 --> 01:00:40,420
Subsequently, I was deeply shocked

961
01:00:40,505 --> 01:00:42,005
when a member of the legal
profession came to me

962
01:00:42,089 --> 01:00:44,424
and asked me if I was now
going to wash my hand.

963
01:00:46,219 --> 01:00:48,845
In my long legal career,
I cannot remember a case

964
01:00:48,930 --> 01:00:50,972
where emotions have been so charged.

965
01:00:52,308 --> 01:00:54,226
It falls to me now to appeal to you

966
01:00:54,310 --> 01:00:55,560
the members of the jury,

967
01:00:55,645 --> 01:00:59,064
not to get caught up in
this tide of mass hysteria.

968
01:01:00,024 --> 01:01:04,778
Inspector Dixon admits there are scores
of inconsistencies in the confessions.

969
01:01:05,154 --> 01:01:08,406
My clients contend that
they were forced to confess

970
01:01:08,491 --> 01:01:11,409
through brutality and intimidation.

971
01:01:13,329 --> 01:01:14,955
Now, they may be foolish,

972
01:01:15,540 --> 01:01:17,958
petty thieves, even drug abusers.

973
01:01:19,252 --> 01:01:23,922
But they are not the ruthless bombers
who have terrorized Britain for months.

974
01:01:25,925 --> 01:01:29,678
You should find these
young people not guilty.

975
01:01:30,304 --> 01:01:32,305
- Bollocks!
- Okay, let's go.

976
01:01:33,057 --> 01:01:35,267
Get your fucking hands off me! Move it!

977
01:01:37,478 --> 01:01:40,772
Hands off.
Hands off! Hands off!

978
01:01:44,110 --> 01:01:45,360
Ladies and gentlemen,

979
01:01:47,488 --> 01:01:50,240
like my learned colleague
in the defense,

980
01:01:50,741 --> 01:01:54,202
I would caution you not to
be swayed by your emotions.

981
01:01:55,246 --> 01:01:58,123
The four people you see in the front

982
01:01:58,833 --> 01:02:02,919
are one of the most cunning and
cruel criminal conspiracies

983
01:02:03,004 --> 01:02:05,380
ever to set foot on English soil.

984
01:02:06,924 --> 01:02:09,092
Now, here are the facts
of this case...

985
01:02:09,677 --> 01:02:11,177
Inspector Dixon,

986
01:02:11,262 --> 01:02:13,638
a decorated officer
of great expertise,

987
01:02:13,723 --> 01:02:17,142
acting on reliable information
and good detective work,

988
01:02:17,226 --> 01:02:19,019
arrested Paul Hill.

989
01:02:19,562 --> 01:02:23,607
Who, guilt-ridden by the shame
of his crime, confessed.

990
01:02:24,567 --> 01:02:28,612
That confession led the police
to the ringleader, Conlon,

991
01:02:28,696 --> 01:02:30,822
and his terrorist family.

992
01:02:31,365 --> 01:02:35,744
His aunt, Annie Maguire,
the experienced bomb maker

993
01:02:35,995 --> 01:02:38,872
who wore rubber gloves
when handling explosives

994
01:02:38,956 --> 01:02:41,583
in the kitchen
of her home in Harlesden.

995
01:02:41,667 --> 01:02:44,127
She even allowed her children
to handle explosives.

996
01:02:44,211 --> 01:02:47,797
Vincent, aged 16, Patrick, 14,

997
01:02:47,882 --> 01:02:51,259
who did not...
Could not know any better.

998
01:02:52,386 --> 01:02:54,638
Guiseppe Conlon,
her brother-in-law,

999
01:02:54,722 --> 01:02:57,599
the courier who arrived
with more explosives.

1000
01:02:57,683 --> 01:03:01,686
Armstrong and his dupe,
Richardson, who carried the bomb.

1001
01:03:01,979 --> 01:03:04,314
Now, these are the people
who, in a panic,

1002
01:03:04,398 --> 01:03:07,400
had to dispose of the nitroglycerine.

1003
01:03:08,736 --> 01:03:11,237
And that is what sealed their fate.

1004
01:03:12,198 --> 01:03:13,740
How do we know this?

1005
01:03:13,824 --> 01:03:16,034
Because the truth was on their hands.

1006
01:03:19,538 --> 01:03:23,416
It is a story written in the
blood of their victims.

1007
01:03:24,377 --> 01:03:26,711
You have seen some of those
who survived

1008
01:03:26,796 --> 01:03:29,464
their callous disregard
for human life.

1009
01:03:30,549 --> 01:03:34,344
It is now your duty
to protect society from them.

1010
01:03:35,554 --> 01:03:38,807
I am confident that
that is what you will do.

1011
01:04:15,511 --> 01:04:16,761
Have you reached a verdict?

