Gerry, man.

1095
01:11:38,912 --> 01:11:40,830
Problem? You all right?

1096
01:11:44,418 --> 01:11:45,918
How do you like your new home?

1097
01:11:46,420 --> 01:11:49,172
Bombing of pillar-box,
Kensington High Street.

1098
01:11:49,256 --> 01:11:50,923
Bombing of pillar-box,
Talbot Lodge.

1099
01:11:51,466 --> 01:11:52,842
Bombing of naval club.

1100
01:11:52,926 --> 01:11:54,510
Bombing of Aldershot Railway Station.

1101
01:11:54,595 --> 01:11:55,887
Attempted murder of Edward Heath.

1102
01:11:56,471 --> 01:11:58,472
Murder of Ross McWhirter.

1103
01:11:58,557 --> 01:12:02,393
Possession of firearms, Balcombe
Street, December 6, 1975.

1104
01:12:02,728 --> 01:12:05,021
And the Guildford pub bombings.

1105
01:12:06,565 --> 01:12:09,358
You have innocent people
in jail for that.

1106
01:12:12,446 --> 01:12:14,238
Take him out.

1107
01:12:37,971 --> 01:12:39,305
He did it.

1108
01:12:41,475 --> 01:12:42,475
Where's all the missing pieces?

1109
01:12:46,396 --> 01:12:48,064
We eat it up, man.

1110
01:12:49,274 --> 01:12:52,860
Before my woman
send it in here, right,

1111
01:12:53,362 --> 01:12:55,613
she have it dipped in liquid acid.

1112
01:12:56,323 --> 01:12:57,990
LSD, man.

1113
01:12:58,659 --> 01:13:02,036
We've been dropping the British
Empire for the last six months.

1114
01:13:02,204 --> 01:13:04,538
You want to fly?
Pick a country.

1115
01:13:04,665 --> 01:13:06,082
Fuck's sake, don't give
me Northern Ireland.

1116
01:13:06,166 --> 01:13:08,125
I don't want a bad trip.

1117
01:13:08,210 --> 01:13:11,087
Try Nepal, man.
Take you to the Himalayas.

1118
01:13:28,146 --> 01:13:30,356
See the dragon.

1119
01:13:56,300 --> 01:13:59,218
- Lights out in 15 minutes.
- Fifteen minutes.

1120
01:14:10,272 --> 01:14:12,398
Are you praying
for the Seventh Cavalry?

1121
01:14:14,985 --> 01:14:16,986
Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

1122
01:14:17,070 --> 01:14:18,195
Blessed art thou amongst women,

1123
01:14:18,280 --> 01:14:20,656
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

1124
01:14:20,741 --> 01:14:22,450
Holy Mary, mother of God,
pray for us sinners

1125
01:14:22,576 --> 01:14:25,119
now and at the moment
of our death. Amen.

1126
01:14:25,203 --> 01:14:26,746
That's not funny, Gerry.

1127
01:14:28,582 --> 01:14:31,250
Hail Mary, full of grace,

1128
01:14:32,252 --> 01:14:33,252
the Lord is with thee.

1129
01:14:35,047 --> 01:14:37,173
Blessed art thou among women

1130
01:14:37,257 --> 01:14:39,425
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

1131
01:14:42,888 --> 01:14:44,805
Holy Mary, mother of God,

1132
01:14:44,890 --> 01:14:48,225
pray for us sinners, now and at
the hour of our death. Amen.

1133
01:14:48,310 --> 01:14:50,144
Hail Mary, full of grace...

1134
01:14:57,110 --> 01:14:58,778
Are you on drugs?

1135
01:15:10,916 --> 01:15:15,211
Look, Da, I'll be older than you are
now when I get out of this place.

1136
01:15:17,089 --> 01:15:18,547
If I get out.

1137
01:15:22,677 --> 01:15:23,803
Are you listening to me?

1138
01:15:24,471 --> 01:15:26,222
I'm not talking to you.

1139
01:15:26,807 --> 01:15:28,808
Now who's being childish?

1140
01:15:30,519 --> 01:15:33,979
I haven't had a sensible word
out of you for two weeks.

1141
01:15:35,732 --> 01:15:36,941
That stuff will kill you.

1142
01:15:38,485 --> 01:15:40,361
Sure, I'm dead anyway.

1143
01:15:44,741 --> 01:15:46,325
Look, I'm sorry.

1144
01:15:46,618 --> 01:15:49,537
I'll not take it again
so long as you live.

1145
01:15:50,497 --> 01:15:52,164
Are you happy now?

1146
01:15:54,376 --> 01:15:55,418
No.

1147
01:15:56,711 --> 01:15:57,962
Why not?

1148
01:16:01,174 --> 01:16:03,592
I don't want you to take it
whether I live or die.

1149
01:16:07,097 --> 01:16:09,598
Jesus Christ.

1150
01:16:14,604 --> 01:16:18,065
All right. I'll do nothing
to annoy you in your grave.

1151
01:16:20,026 --> 01:16:21,694
Now are you happy?

1152
01:16:22,779 --> 01:16:23,904
Is that a promise?

1153
01:16:27,868 --> 01:16:29,034
Aye.

1154
01:16:30,662 --> 01:16:31,912
Maybe.

1155
01:16:40,046 --> 01:16:42,548
Gerry, man, check out your friend.

1156
01:16:45,093 --> 01:16:46,760
He look like the real thing.

1157
01:16:51,183 --> 01:16:52,391
Come on.

1158
01:17:04,446 --> 01:17:06,363
Excuse me.
All right.

1159
01:17:09,951 --> 01:17:11,619
Let's have a talk.

1160
01:17:15,582 --> 01:17:17,708
We have to eat in the cells.

1161
01:17:18,877 --> 01:17:20,336
See ya later.

1162
01:17:22,005 --> 01:17:24,131
Gerry. Gerry, come on.

1163
01:17:50,617 --> 01:17:52,117
Morning, paddy.

1164
01:17:57,624 --> 01:17:58,707
Yes!

1165
01:18:06,800 --> 01:18:08,008
Come on!

1166
01:18:08,927 --> 01:18:10,261
Yes, man, Gerry!

1167
01:18:21,022 --> 01:18:24,650
This one, this one, this one,
14 days solitary! Lock up!

1168
01:18:25,527 --> 01:18:26,819
Lock up!

1169
01:18:27,654 --> 01:18:29,989
He'll be all right.
He'll be back in a couple of days.

1170
01:18:40,584 --> 01:18:42,585
I'm worried about Bridie.

1171
01:18:45,213 --> 01:18:46,297
Why?

1172
01:18:48,049 --> 01:18:50,175
She's dyed her hair blonde.

1173
01:18:52,137 --> 01:18:54,013
Well, she's only young.

1174
01:18:57,684 --> 01:18:59,810
She's wearing a dog collar.

1175
01:19:07,360 --> 01:19:10,613
There's a fella chained to it.
He's got one on, too.

1176
01:19:14,284 --> 01:19:15,492
Well...

1177
01:19:16,494 --> 01:19:18,370
As long as she's happy.

1178
01:19:29,841 --> 01:19:31,216
Lunch break.

1179
01:19:33,928 --> 01:19:36,180
Yes, Gerry, man!
That's right!

1180
01:19:36,431 --> 01:19:38,098
Gerry's a bad boy!

1181
01:19:39,017 --> 01:19:41,393
Put the Englishman on their
heavy, heavy manners.

1182
01:19:41,603 --> 01:19:45,189
Yes, sir. Go on, boy.
Kick out them clods, yes?

1183
01:19:46,483 --> 01:19:49,276
This is Joe McAndrew.
He has something important to tell you.

1184
01:19:49,569 --> 01:19:50,694
Hello, Mr. Conlon.

1185
01:19:53,365 --> 01:19:54,990
I'm watching you.

1186
01:20:06,586 --> 01:20:07,961
What is it?

1187
01:20:08,922 --> 01:20:12,424
I'm the one who planted the
Guildford bomb, Mr. Conlon.

1188
01:20:15,470 --> 01:20:17,680
Did you tell the police that?

1189
01:20:17,764 --> 01:20:19,098
Yes, I did.

1190
01:20:20,767 --> 01:20:21,892
But we haven't heard a thing.

1191
01:20:21,976 --> 01:20:23,936
Will you just wait and see
what he has to say, Da?

1192
01:20:25,146 --> 01:20:26,313
Go on.

1193
01:20:27,482 --> 01:20:30,275
I told them. They know...
They know the truth.

1194
01:20:31,945 --> 01:20:34,113
They can't afford to face it.

1195
01:20:34,614 --> 01:20:37,866
It's a war.
You're one if its innocent victims.

1196
01:20:37,951 --> 01:20:40,035
I'm sorry for your trouble.

1197
01:20:40,120 --> 01:20:41,995
Don't be sorry for us.

1198
01:20:42,997 --> 01:20:44,540
You should be sorry
for the people you killed.

1199
01:20:46,418 --> 01:20:49,294
It was a military target,
a soldiers' pub.

1200
01:20:50,004 --> 01:20:53,841
They were innocent people,
God's children.

1201
01:20:54,426 --> 01:20:58,512
Look, I'll do all I can to
help you while you're in here.

1202
01:20:58,888 --> 01:20:59,972
We don't need your help.

1203
01:21:01,933 --> 01:21:04,184
I'd appreciate it
if you'd leave us alone.

1204
01:21:05,645 --> 01:21:07,271
Whatever you say.

1205
01:21:10,442 --> 01:21:12,234
I'm sorry about that.

1206
01:21:16,197 --> 01:21:17,948
What was that all about?
You mind your fucking manners.

1207
01:21:18,324 --> 01:21:20,284
What? Manners to him?

1208
01:21:20,827 --> 01:21:22,369
I don't want any part
of him, or his ways.

1209
01:21:22,454 --> 01:21:23,912
At least he stands up for himself.
At least he fights back,

1210
01:21:23,997 --> 01:21:25,164
which is more than you
ever did in your life.

1211
01:21:25,248 --> 01:21:26,582
What are you talking about?

1212
01:21:26,666 --> 01:21:28,333
Do you remember Lydon Hill?
Huh?

1213
01:21:29,002 --> 01:21:31,503
You used to ride me up on the
crossbar of your bike up Lydon Hill.

1214
01:21:32,130 --> 01:21:33,464
And then one day you
couldn't make it to the top,

1215
01:21:33,548 --> 01:21:36,133
and I hopped off the crossbar,
and I looked back,

1216
01:21:36,217 --> 01:21:38,051
and your face was all red.

1217
01:21:38,136 --> 01:21:39,928
Remember that?
Aye.

1218
01:21:42,891 --> 01:21:45,476
It was working in the paint
shed done that to you.

1219
01:21:45,560 --> 01:21:46,602
What?

1220
01:21:46,686 --> 01:21:50,314
It was the fumes from working in
the paint shed done that to you.

1221
01:21:50,398 --> 01:21:52,858
Never mind jumping off the ferry
and swimming back to Mummy.

1222
01:21:52,942 --> 01:21:54,777
It was the one job a Catholic can get,

1223
01:21:54,861 --> 01:21:56,361
and you wouldn't even fight back then.

1224
01:21:57,155 --> 01:21:58,655
Go on outside.

1225
01:21:59,783 --> 01:22:01,450
Play with your newfound friend.

1226
01:22:02,285 --> 01:22:04,119
Look, all I'm saying is that you've
been a victim all your life.

1227
01:22:04,204 --> 01:22:05,871
It's about time
you started to fight back.

1228
01:22:05,955 --> 01:22:07,581
Get out of my sight.
I'm going.

1229
01:22:11,085 --> 01:22:14,171
This is the only way it'll work.
We have no alternative.

1230
01:22:31,064 --> 01:22:32,523
Well, what are you doing?

1231
01:22:32,607 --> 01:22:33,690
Nothing.

1232
01:22:35,485 --> 01:22:37,152
They didn't do it.

1233
01:22:37,237 --> 01:22:38,237
They all did it.

1234
01:22:41,991 --> 01:22:44,034
I'm going back to Belfast.

1235
01:22:50,708 --> 01:22:52,251
After the fight, nobody stopped us

1236
01:22:52,335 --> 01:22:54,378
going out in the yard to exercise.

1237
01:22:54,462 --> 01:22:56,088
I felt brilliant.

1238
01:22:56,256 --> 01:22:57,673
Joe explained things to me.

1239
01:22:57,757 --> 01:23:00,843
He explained how the Brits never
left anywhere without a fight.

1240
01:23:00,927 --> 01:23:04,388
How they had to be beaten out of
every country they ever occupied.

1241
01:23:04,472 --> 01:23:07,683
How this prison was just
an extension of their system.

1242
01:23:07,767 --> 01:23:10,352
Calling for work on the threes.

1243
01:23:10,770 --> 01:23:13,856
We had to confront the chief
prison officer, Barker.

1244
01:23:13,940 --> 01:23:15,023
Mr. Smalls.

1245
01:23:15,108 --> 01:23:17,943
But to do that, we had to
take care of Ronnie Smalls.

1246
01:23:18,236 --> 01:23:20,904
Can I have a word
about 54, Halsley Road?

1247
01:23:24,659 --> 01:23:26,076
Take a walk.

1248
01:23:34,294 --> 01:23:37,170
If anything happens to me or Gerry

1249
01:23:38,548 --> 01:23:40,674
or any other Irish prisoner,

1250
01:23:41,509 --> 01:23:45,220
we'll have 54, Halsley Road
blown to smithereens

1251
01:23:45,889 --> 01:23:47,806
with your family in it.

1252
01:23:49,809 --> 01:23:52,477
Threaten my family and I'll
cut your fucking head off.

1253
01:23:56,190 --> 01:23:57,774
I don't make threats.

1254
01:23:57,859 --> 01:23:59,818
I just carry out orders.

1255
01:24:00,320 --> 01:24:01,862
I don't want to hurt your family.

1256
01:24:07,118 --> 01:24:10,704
Your trouble is, Joe, you want
to rule the fucking world.

1257
01:24:12,624 --> 01:24:13,749
Paddy's all right.

1258
01:24:25,595 --> 01:24:28,388
Soon, we were all one happy family.

1259
01:24:28,514 --> 01:24:29,556
Again!

1260
01:24:29,641 --> 01:24:31,975
Even Kojak was ready to forgive.

1261
01:24:32,226 --> 01:24:33,560
Live and let live.

1262
01:24:33,686 --> 01:24:34,937
Barker began to panic.

1263
01:24:35,730 --> 01:24:37,814
He told us to take our socks
out of the window.

1264
01:24:37,899 --> 01:24:40,442
He thought we were signaling
to other prisoners.

1265
01:24:40,735 --> 01:24:43,487
We're not signaling.
We're drying our socks out.

1266
01:24:43,571 --> 01:24:45,322
Take the socks out of the window.
Who says?

1267
01:24:45,657 --> 01:24:46,823
Mr. Barker.

1268
01:24:46,908 --> 01:24:49,201
That was all the excuse Joe needed.

1269
01:24:49,285 --> 01:24:50,535
Give us two minutes.

1270
01:24:51,079 --> 01:24:53,163
- Hey, up and away we went.
- Are you with me?

1271
01:24:53,456 --> 01:24:54,581
What's he up to now?

1272
01:24:58,461 --> 01:25:00,796
All prison officers
to vacate the wing.

1273
01:25:01,172 --> 01:25:03,298
All officers vacate the wing!

1274
01:25:09,681 --> 01:25:11,181
This'll damage the whole campaign.

1275
01:25:11,265 --> 01:25:13,684
Look, you do it your way, and
we'll do it ours, all right?

1276
01:25:13,893 --> 01:25:15,310
You can read our demands.

1277
01:25:15,561 --> 01:25:17,562
Go back to your cells.

1278
01:25:17,939 --> 01:25:19,231
Blankets!

1279
01:25:19,899 --> 01:25:21,817
For God's sake, put a stop to this.

1280
01:25:21,901 --> 01:25:23,735
You're weakening
my position, Guiseppe.

1281
01:25:23,820 --> 01:25:25,696
It will end in violence.
Good.

1282
01:25:25,780 --> 01:25:26,947
What's good about it?

1283
01:25:27,031 --> 01:25:28,115
It's all they understand.

1284
01:25:31,202 --> 01:25:33,161
Barker refused to negotiate.

1285
01:25:33,246 --> 01:25:35,455
But with the screws gone,
we'd a brief taste of freedom.

1286
01:25:35,540 --> 01:25:36,748
Check out Ronnie!

1287
01:25:38,918 --> 01:25:40,252
Him swallow half Africa.

1288
01:25:42,088 --> 01:25:43,463
I give him about an hour.

1289
01:25:50,054 --> 01:25:52,723
We found out later
our protest got on TV.

1290
01:25:53,391 --> 01:25:55,267
And that's when the riot
squad was ordered in.

1291
01:25:57,895 --> 01:25:58,979
Shh!

1292
01:26:11,242 --> 01:26:13,118
We were singled out
as the ringleaders.

1293
01:26:13,453 --> 01:26:14,494
Now!

1294
01:26:40,063 --> 01:26:42,147
You just signed your own
death warrant, Barker.

1295
01:26:46,986 --> 01:26:48,111
Are you happy now?

1296
01:26:52,325 --> 01:26:54,534
And then you arrived, Gareth.

1297
01:26:54,786 --> 01:26:58,914
That's the first time I saw you,
under a raining shower of sparks.

1298
01:26:58,998 --> 01:27:02,876
It was the first time I'd seen a woman
in five years, other than my mother.

1299
01:27:02,960 --> 01:27:05,212
But to me, you were a lawyer first.

1300
01:27:05,296 --> 01:27:06,505
And I hated lawyers.

1301
01:27:06,589 --> 01:27:07,923
And do you have a new isolation room?

1302
01:27:08,007 --> 01:27:09,674
Prisoners!

1303
01:27:10,093 --> 01:27:11,927
Bert, Andrew.

1304
01:27:12,178 --> 01:27:15,347
Bailey, Benjamin.
McAndrew, Joseph.

1305
01:27:15,431 --> 01:27:17,849
Sorry. Can you... I can't hear.
Conlon, Gerard.

1306
01:27:18,226 --> 01:27:19,893
O'Brien, John.

1307
01:27:20,520 --> 01:27:23,939
Lynch, Bernard.
Crisp, Quincy.

1308
01:27:24,232 --> 01:27:27,150
Lyon, Richard.
Burns, Delrow.

1309
01:27:27,360 --> 01:27:28,902
What about Conlon?

1310
01:27:28,986 --> 01:27:31,071
Sorry. Guiseppe Conlon.

1311
01:27:31,697 --> 01:27:33,323
He's on the third floor.

1312
01:27:34,283 --> 01:27:37,035
He has difficulty
getting down the stairs.

1313
01:27:38,538 --> 01:27:41,081
Well, I'll just have to
go up and see him then.

1314
01:27:41,165 --> 01:27:43,708
The delegation has seen enough.
Right-o. Sorry.

1315
01:27:44,043 --> 01:27:47,045
Well, I won't be a minute. I'll just...
Is that all right? Sorry.

1316
01:27:48,089 --> 01:27:50,507
I'll meet you outside, okay?
Sorry.

1317
01:27:57,306 --> 01:27:58,473
Sorry, I can't...

1318
01:27:58,558 --> 01:27:59,724
Pulmonary thrombosis.

1319
01:27:59,809 --> 01:28:01,143
Uh-huh. And you're
getting medication...

1320
01:28:01,227 --> 01:28:02,310
He's getting proper medication?

1321
01:28:02,395 --> 01:28:03,478
Are you? Yes?

1322
01:28:04,063 --> 01:28:05,063
Uh-huh.

1323
01:28:08,901 --> 01:28:09,901
Son?

1324
01:28:10,403 --> 01:28:11,570
Gerry!

1325
01:28:12,738 --> 01:28:14,614
That's... Is it Gerry?

1326
01:28:14,699 --> 01:28:15,949
That's Gerry.
Uh-huh.

1327
01:28:16,033 --> 01:28:18,368
He's had a spot of bother
with lawyers in the past.

1328
01:28:22,415 --> 01:28:24,916
He's all yours.
Fifteen minutes.

1329
01:28:25,668 --> 01:28:27,043
Thank you.
Sit down.

1330
01:28:34,635 --> 01:28:36,011
You wanted to see me, Gerry?

1331
01:28:57,074 --> 01:28:59,367
Why are you giving
my father false hope?

1332
01:29:00,203 --> 01:29:01,369
Sorry?

1333
01:29:02,205 --> 01:29:04,456
He's been up and down these stairs
every couple of weeks to see you.

1334
01:29:04,540 --> 01:29:06,333
He hasn't even seen
my mother in six months.

1335
01:29:06,417 --> 01:29:09,586
Oh, I hear you're getting on
very well with her, by the way.

1336
01:29:09,670 --> 01:29:11,796
Yes. She's a very
brave woman.

1337
01:29:12,381 --> 01:29:13,715
Aye, you don't know the half of it.

1338
01:29:16,928 --> 01:29:18,303
The fucking stairs are killing him.

1339
01:29:19,055 --> 01:29:21,139
It's not the stairs that are
killing your father, Gerry.

1340
01:29:21,641 --> 01:29:22,974
Why, what is it, then?

1341
01:29:23,059 --> 01:29:24,351
It's your lack of faith.

1342
01:29:25,144 --> 01:29:27,395
Lack of faith?
Faith in what?

1343
01:29:28,022 --> 01:29:29,189
In yourself.

1344
01:29:29,482 --> 01:29:32,025
No, I have faith in myself.

1345
01:29:33,486 --> 01:29:37,155
Gerry Conlon, lifer,
30-year sentence.

1346
01:29:37,615 --> 01:29:39,199
And I know how to survive it.
No problem.

1347
01:29:40,993 --> 01:29:42,160
At what price?

1348
01:29:42,495 --> 01:29:44,579
I'll pay the fucking price.
Don't you worry about it.

1349
01:29:45,498 --> 01:29:47,249
The price for what?

1350
01:29:47,333 --> 01:29:48,583
Right.

1351
01:29:49,502 --> 01:29:52,045
You're very good at the
English, aren't you?

1352
01:29:52,922 --> 01:29:55,715
You see, I don't understand
your language.

1353
01:29:57,635 --> 01:30:00,720
Justice. Mercy. Clemency.

1354
01:30:01,347 --> 01:30:04,599
I literally don't understand
what those words mean.

1355
01:30:05,101 --> 01:30:08,103
You see, I'd like to put in an application
to get all my teeth extracted.

1356
01:30:08,187 --> 01:30:09,938
And that way I could put
my fist in my mouth

1357
01:30:10,022 --> 01:30:12,649
and never speak another word of
fuckin' English so long as I live...

1358
01:30:12,733 --> 01:30:14,859
Do you see what I'm saying, Miss Peirce?
Mrs. Peirce, is it?

1359
01:30:15,903 --> 01:30:17,404
Are you trying to impress me?

1360
01:30:19,573 --> 01:30:20,865
Visit's up.

1361
01:30:21,534 --> 01:30:24,369
Don't give my father
false hope, all right?

1362
01:30:24,662 --> 01:30:26,371
Gerry!

1363
01:30:27,707 --> 01:30:29,374
Well, you've got to help him!

1364
01:30:31,752 --> 01:30:34,796
In prison, you pray for
anything to break the monotony.

1365
01:30:34,880 --> 01:30:37,549
A snowstorm is like
a present from God.

1366
01:30:42,888 --> 01:30:44,055
Whoo!

1367
01:30:46,976 --> 01:30:48,560
Stop!

1368
01:30:48,644 --> 01:30:49,978
Prison officers are not to be hit!

1369
01:30:50,896 --> 01:30:52,564
All right, you lot,
you've asked for it.

1370
01:30:52,898 --> 01:30:54,399
Come along!

1371
01:30:55,234 --> 01:30:58,111
After the riot, my father's
health deteriorated badly.

1372
01:30:58,696 --> 01:31:01,656
He couldn't make it down
the stairs to enjoy the snow.

1373
01:31:01,741 --> 01:31:05,118
I waved up to him, but he was
looking at something else.

1374
01:31:15,379 --> 01:31:17,380
My da always saw the good in people.

1375
01:31:18,090 --> 01:31:21,259
He recognized it in you the
minute he saw you, Gareth.

1376
01:31:21,677 --> 01:31:23,011
Guv, guv, where you going?

1377
01:31:23,095 --> 01:31:25,430
Where's me letters? Guv'nor!

1378
01:31:29,560 --> 01:31:30,894
Thank you.

1379
01:31:35,358 --> 01:31:38,234
I see you've been mentioned
in Congress, Guiseppe.

1380
01:31:38,319 --> 01:31:39,736
What's that?

1381
01:31:46,619 --> 01:31:47,827
How'd you come by that name?

1382
01:31:48,287 --> 01:31:51,373
What?
An Italian ice cream maker.

1383
01:31:51,749 --> 01:31:54,918
Had a shop on the corner of
the street where I was born.

1384
01:31:55,002 --> 01:31:56,544
Guiseppe Fosco.

1385
01:31:57,338 --> 01:31:59,881
My mother fell in love with the name.

1386
01:31:59,965 --> 01:32:01,132
Were they...

1387
01:32:02,885 --> 01:32:04,219
You know.
What?

1388
01:32:05,638 --> 01:32:07,222
Lovers.
Who?

1389
01:32:07,640 --> 01:32:09,224
My mother and the Italian
ice cream maker?

1390
01:32:10,309 --> 01:32:12,185
Oh, no, God.

1391
01:32:12,269 --> 01:32:14,687
Jesus, no.
No, they were not.

1392
01:32:15,815 --> 01:32:17,941
No, she just liked the name.

1393
01:32:19,235 --> 01:32:21,236
But it made my life hell.

1394
01:32:21,821 --> 01:32:24,489
All the other children
laughing at you.

1395
01:32:24,990 --> 01:32:27,117
You have any kids yourself?

1396
01:32:30,162 --> 01:32:31,496
He's talking to Barker now.

1397
01:32:31,872 --> 01:32:34,958
Forget it, Joe. He can talk
to whoever he fucking likes.

1398
01:32:37,920 --> 01:32:39,003
Two.

1399
01:32:40,840 --> 01:32:42,549
Flown the nest now.

1400
01:32:59,859 --> 01:33:01,693
Whether Barker was responsible or not

1401
01:33:01,777 --> 01:33:05,029
for bringing in the riot squad,
Joe never forgave him.

1402
01:33:06,490 --> 01:33:08,533
Joe was still at war.

1403
01:33:08,617 --> 01:33:10,952
And to him, Barker was the enemy.

1404
01:33:12,830 --> 01:33:14,164
Number?

1405
01:33:14,790 --> 01:33:16,124
The name is McAndrew.

1406
01:33:18,169 --> 01:33:20,253
Get out... Get out of the
way, out of the light.

1407
01:33:21,922 --> 01:33:22,964
Get out of the light.

1408
01:33:23,048 --> 01:33:24,007
Number?

1409
01:33:24,091 --> 01:33:25,508
Name's Gerry Conlon.

1410
01:33:27,803 --> 01:33:29,721
Piss off out of the light.
Get out of the light!

1411
01:33:30,264 --> 01:33:31,639
You're 136.

1412
01:33:37,396 --> 01:33:39,689
There's someone sitting there.

1413
01:33:41,942 --> 01:33:44,277
Move when you're told.

1414
01:33:50,367 --> 01:33:51,493
Put it out.

1415
01:34:22,107 --> 01:34:23,233
How's your boy?

1416
01:34:23,317 --> 01:34:24,400
He's good.

1417
01:34:24,485 --> 01:34:27,237
You know, he looks
more like you every day.

1418
01:34:27,947 --> 01:34:29,822
He's smarter than I am.

1419
01:34:30,407 --> 01:34:31,950
Three years old,
he can read the funny papers.

1420
01:34:32,117 --> 01:34:34,118
There's a hair
in the fucking projector!

1421
01:34:34,328 --> 01:34:37,080
Yeah, get the fucking hair
out the projector, will you?

1422
01:34:38,874 --> 01:34:40,083
Come on. Get it out!

1423
01:34:40,459 --> 01:34:41,584
Get it out!

1424
01:34:43,671 --> 01:34:46,923
I'm going fucking blind up here, guv.
Lively!

1425
01:34:53,639 --> 01:34:55,265
We'll get there, Pop.
Quiet.

1426
01:34:55,349 --> 01:34:57,267
I didn't say a fucking thing.
You're blocking.

1427
01:34:57,351 --> 01:34:58,601
Shut it.

1428
01:35:10,990 --> 01:35:14,242
I knew that Santino was gonna
have to go through all this.

1429
01:35:15,327 --> 01:35:17,579
And Fredo, well...

1430
01:35:19,623 --> 01:35:21,207
Fredo was wrong.

1431
01:35:23,335 --> 01:35:26,170
And I never...
I never wanted this for you.

1432
01:35:29,258 --> 01:35:30,341
Oi, you!

1433
01:35:59,496 --> 01:36:02,415
Barker! Move back, Barker!

1434
01:36:02,833 --> 01:36:03,958
Get in there!

1435
01:36:04,043 --> 01:36:05,501
Get it out!

1436
01:36:27,399 --> 01:36:28,483
Stretcher!

1437
01:36:28,567 --> 01:36:29,651
Let's check this out.

1438
01:36:30,069 --> 01:36:32,070
All right, mate.
You're with us.

1439
01:36:32,154 --> 01:36:33,696
All right. Stretcher!

1440
01:36:35,491 --> 01:36:36,616
Gently, now.

1441
01:36:36,992 --> 01:36:38,493
Come on, up!

1442
01:36:39,536 --> 01:36:41,704
That was a good day's work, McAndrew.

1443
01:36:42,539 --> 01:36:43,831
That was a good day's work.

1444
01:36:44,458 --> 01:36:46,084
Get away from me.

1445
01:36:46,919 --> 01:36:49,253
Will you not look me in the
eye when I'm speaking to you?

1446
01:36:52,049 --> 01:36:54,926
See, I know how to look at
people without blinking as well.

1447
01:36:58,764 --> 01:37:01,182
In all my godforsaken life,
I've never known

1448
01:37:01,266 --> 01:37:04,560
what it was like to want
to kill somebody until now.

1449
01:37:07,189 --> 01:37:09,816
You're a brave man, Joe, a brave man.

1450
01:37:12,611 --> 01:37:15,029
Gerard Conlon, back on the threes.

1451
01:37:15,447 --> 01:37:16,406
Stand your ground.

1452
01:37:16,490 --> 01:37:19,158
Hawkins, returning to his cell.

1453
01:37:19,493 --> 01:37:21,577
Benjamin Bailey, back to his cell!

1454
01:37:22,204 --> 01:37:24,163
Benjamin Bailey,
returning to his cell.

1455
01:37:24,248 --> 01:37:26,791
7445, Casey, back to his cell.

1456
01:37:26,875 --> 01:37:29,419
6309, Johnston, level three.

1457
01:37:29,795 --> 01:37:32,630
Regis, 113, going up to number two.

1458
01:37:50,274 --> 01:37:52,358
- Back to your cell now!
- Keep moving.

1459
01:37:53,485 --> 01:37:55,236
Barker was maimed for life

1460
01:37:55,320 --> 01:37:57,739
and Joe was sent to another prison.

1461
01:37:58,157 --> 01:37:59,824
He's in solitary confinement
somewhere.

1462
01:37:59,908 --> 01:38:02,452
We've had no news of him since then.

1463
01:38:02,745 --> 01:38:05,371
The new chief screw
had the yard painted

1464
01:38:05,456 --> 01:38:07,373
and I was back
walking in circles again.

1465
01:38:07,458 --> 01:38:09,125
Back to the cells.

1466
01:38:11,211 --> 01:38:12,712
Come on. Move.

1467
01:38:41,325 --> 01:38:44,118
I'd like to help you out
with the campaign, Da...

1468
01:38:45,746 --> 01:38:47,955
If that's all right with you.

1469
01:38:48,582 --> 01:38:49,916
Do you mean it?

1470
01:38:50,542 --> 01:38:51,626
Aye.

1471
01:38:52,544 --> 01:38:54,128
That's great.

1472
01:38:54,588 --> 01:38:56,923
Okay, Gerry, what I need
from you is the whole story,

1473
01:38:57,007 --> 01:38:59,926
your whole story, in as much
detail as you can remember.

1474
01:39:00,010 --> 01:39:02,386
Every detail you can think of,
and I need you to write it down.

1475
01:39:02,471 --> 01:39:04,388
It's really important.

1476
01:39:10,771 --> 01:39:12,396
I can't do this.

1477
01:39:15,067 --> 01:39:16,442
I can't write this, Da.

1478
01:39:16,819 --> 01:39:18,319
Could your son not give you a hand?

1479
01:39:18,403 --> 01:39:21,405
Nah. He's up in his
cell writing away.

1480
01:39:26,829 --> 01:39:27,912
Okay.

1481
01:39:33,710 --> 01:39:35,044
Tape recorder.

1482
01:39:35,128 --> 01:39:37,421
You're...
You're a good talker.

1483
01:39:38,006 --> 01:39:39,090
Talk.

1484
01:39:40,801 --> 01:39:42,677
The strange thing is...

1485
01:39:44,096 --> 01:39:46,180
The strange thing is sometimes
I think he's a little jealous

1486
01:39:46,265 --> 01:39:48,933
of me taking over
the campaign and that there.

1487
01:39:49,017 --> 01:39:51,769
Going up and down the stairs
to meet you.

1488
01:39:52,729 --> 01:39:55,356
That's something I never
thought about Guiseppe,

1489
01:39:55,440 --> 01:39:57,441
that he could be jealous.

1490
01:39:59,111 --> 01:40:02,363
Anyhow, the main thing is
to get the case reopened

1491
01:40:03,240 --> 01:40:06,617
because I don't know how long
he can survive in here.

1492
01:40:23,802 --> 01:40:25,177
I'm tired of this.

1493
01:40:26,054 --> 01:40:27,680
Come on. We have to do this.
Come on.

1494
01:40:27,931 --> 01:40:29,265
You behave yourself.

1495
01:40:33,645 --> 01:40:34,770
Get your head down.

1496
01:40:42,154 --> 01:40:45,364
When I was a wee lad, I used to wonder
what you were doing under the towel.

1497
01:40:45,449 --> 01:40:47,033
And one day when you and Ma were out,

1498
01:40:47,117 --> 01:40:48,868
I got a big bowl of boiling water,

1499
01:40:48,952 --> 01:40:52,288
whacked a big drop of Vicks and
then put the towel over my head.

1500
01:40:52,372 --> 01:40:53,998
And then I sat there trying to
figure out what it was all about

1501
01:40:54,082 --> 01:40:56,334
'cause nothing was happening.

1502
01:40:56,418 --> 01:40:58,377
And then I figured you must've been drinking it.
Do you remember that?

1503
01:40:58,462 --> 01:41:00,338
So I stuck my tongue in it.
Do you remember that?

1504
01:41:03,675 --> 01:41:05,426
How could I forget?

1505
01:41:06,428 --> 01:41:09,347
And your tongue
swelled up like a football.

1506
01:41:10,515 --> 01:41:12,475
Had to rush you to the hospital.

1507
01:41:12,559 --> 01:41:14,769
First time you'd stopped
talking in your life.

1508
01:41:18,023 --> 01:41:19,023
Give us that.

1509
01:41:21,026 --> 01:41:23,319
I'll do your chest for you, Da.

1510
01:41:31,161 --> 01:41:32,536
Was I always bad, was I?

1511
01:41:34,039 --> 01:41:35,289
Not always.

1512
01:41:35,791 --> 01:41:38,167
I don't deserve to spend the
rest of my life in here, do I?

1513
01:41:39,211 --> 01:41:42,129
All they've done
is block out the light.

1514
01:41:42,214 --> 01:41:43,673
They can't block out
the light in here.

1515
