01:59:49,842 --> 01:59:51,509
Do you know Annie Maguire

1762
01:59:52,595 --> 01:59:55,430
who served her 14 years
without remission?

1763
01:59:56,807 --> 01:59:59,476
Do you know her son Vincent
who served five years?

1764
01:59:59,852 --> 02:00:01,394
Do you know her son Patrick
who served four?

1765
02:00:01,479 --> 02:00:03,646
Do you know her husband,
Paddy Maguire,

1766
02:00:04,190 --> 02:00:05,982
who served 12 years?

1767
02:00:06,859 --> 02:00:10,487
Carole Richardson was 17 when
she went to jail, Mr. Dixon.

1768
02:00:10,780 --> 02:00:12,280
Now she is 32.

1769
02:00:14,533 --> 02:00:15,909
Do you know Carole Richardson?

1770
02:00:15,993 --> 02:00:17,786
My Lord, what is the point of this?

1771
02:00:17,953 --> 02:00:20,371
Yes, come to the point,
Mrs. Peirce.

1772
02:00:27,421 --> 02:00:29,923
Do you know who this is,
Mr. Dixon?

1773
02:00:34,720 --> 02:00:35,887
No, I don't.

1774
02:00:36,847 --> 02:00:39,182
Well, then would you be so kind

1775
02:00:39,266 --> 02:00:41,601
as to read this statement
that you took from him

1776
02:00:41,685 --> 02:00:44,729
on the 3rd of November, 1974?

1777
02:00:44,814 --> 02:00:47,941
A statement, My Lord, which
vindicates all of these people,

1778
02:00:48,025 --> 02:00:49,150
all these innocent people.

1779
02:00:49,235 --> 02:00:50,944
My Lord, I need to see a
copy of this statement.

1780
02:00:51,028 --> 02:00:55,031
Either that man or his superior
or his superior's superior

1781
02:00:55,116 --> 02:00:57,534
ordered that these people
be used as scapegoats

1782
02:00:57,618 --> 02:00:59,577
by a nation that was baying for blood...
Mrs. Peirce!

1783
02:00:59,662 --> 02:01:00,662
My Lord!

1784
02:01:00,746 --> 02:01:04,249
In return for the innocent blood
spilled on the streets of Guildford!

1785
02:01:04,333 --> 02:01:05,625
And by God, you've got
your blood, Mr. Dixon.

1786
02:01:05,709 --> 02:01:07,252
Mrs. Peirce is making
a political speech.

1787
02:01:07,378 --> 02:01:09,045
This is outrageous.
You got the blood of Guiseppe Conlon,

1788
02:01:09,130 --> 02:01:11,047
you got the lifeblood
of Carole Richardson,

1789
02:01:11,132 --> 02:01:14,092
and you got 15 years of blood and
sweat and pain from my client

1790
02:01:14,176 --> 02:01:17,178
whose only crime was that he was Irish.
-Silence in court!

1791
02:01:17,263 --> 02:01:20,140
And he was foolish, and he was in
the wrong place at the wrong time!

1792
02:01:20,224 --> 02:01:23,476
Mrs. Peirce, I will have you
removed from the court.

1793
02:01:29,400 --> 02:01:31,526
And one of your colleagues, My Lord,

1794
02:01:31,610 --> 02:01:33,736
who sat where you sit
now said, and I quote,

1795
02:01:33,821 --> 02:01:36,906
"It is a pity you were not charged
with treason to the Crown,

1796
02:01:36,991 --> 02:01:40,577
"a charge that carries a
penalty of death by hanging.

1797
02:01:40,786 --> 02:01:44,247
"A sentence I would have no
difficulty in passing in this case."

1798
02:01:44,582 --> 02:01:48,042
Mrs. Peirce, I am trying
to read this document.

1799
02:01:48,127 --> 02:01:50,712
I will not tell you again to be silent

1800
02:01:50,796 --> 02:01:54,132
or you will be removed from the court.

1801
02:02:36,258 --> 02:02:38,760
My Lord, this document

1802
02:02:38,844 --> 02:02:41,721
brings the entire British
legal system into disrepute.

1803
02:02:42,014 --> 02:02:44,432
My Lord, this is new evidence.

1804
02:02:44,808 --> 02:02:46,476
It is shocking new evidence.

1805
02:02:46,977 --> 02:02:48,186
My Lord, this evidence

1806
02:02:48,270 --> 02:02:51,481
was not submitted at the
trial that is under appeal.

1807
02:02:51,732 --> 02:02:55,151
That, I believe, is the point that Mrs.
Peirce is trying to make.

1808
02:02:55,361 --> 02:02:56,527
Proceed, Mrs. Peirce.

1809
02:02:56,612 --> 02:02:57,695
My Lord, I demand a recess.

1810
02:02:57,780 --> 02:03:00,990
There will be no demands
made in my court.

1811
02:03:02,201 --> 02:03:03,576
Stand back.

1812
02:03:06,830 --> 02:03:09,999
My Lord, this alibi for Gerry Conlon

1813
02:03:11,085 --> 02:03:12,543
was taken by Mr. Dixon

1814
02:03:12,628 --> 02:03:15,421
one month after
Gerry Conlon was arrested.

1815
02:03:16,257 --> 02:03:20,051
This note was attached to it
when I found it in police files.

1816
02:03:20,344 --> 02:03:22,178
It reads, "Not to be shown
to the defense."

1817
02:03:29,937 --> 02:03:32,605
I have one question
to ask you, Mr. Dixon.

1818
02:03:33,190 --> 02:03:34,983
Why was the alibi for Gerry Conlon,

1819
02:03:35,067 --> 02:03:38,695
who was charged with the murder
of five innocent people,

1820
02:03:39,655 --> 02:03:41,322
kept from the defense?

1821
02:03:49,373 --> 02:03:51,124
- Give us an answer!
- Answer the question!

1822
02:03:51,959 --> 02:03:53,710
Silence!

1823
02:03:53,961 --> 02:03:54,961
It's about time!

1824
02:03:55,045 --> 02:03:56,754
Order in the court!

1825
02:03:58,716 --> 02:04:01,551
My Lord, I would like
to approach the bench.

1826
02:04:01,635 --> 02:04:02,885
This is most irregular.

1827
02:04:03,053 --> 02:04:05,471
Yes. I am aware of that,
My Lord.

1828
02:04:06,557 --> 02:04:07,890
Very well.

1829
02:04:24,450 --> 02:04:26,451
Mr. Dixon,
you may stand down.

1830
02:04:26,535 --> 02:04:28,161
No! No! No!
My Lord!

1831
02:04:28,245 --> 02:04:30,455
My Lord, this is the man
who should be under arrest!

1832
02:04:30,581 --> 02:04:32,749
Be silent,
Mrs. Peirce!

1833
02:04:33,125 --> 02:04:34,625
This court is now in recess.

1834
02:04:34,710 --> 02:04:35,960
Guards, get ready.

1835
02:04:36,253 --> 02:04:38,379
Look, don't try
and make me the fall guy

1836
02:04:38,464 --> 02:04:41,132
for the whole
British legal establishment.

1837
02:04:45,554 --> 02:04:48,222
Look, if I accept this mercy deal...

1838
02:04:48,724 --> 02:04:49,974
They've a flippin' cheek,
offering me mercy.

1839
02:04:50,059 --> 02:04:51,601
I mean, they should be begging
for mercy themselves.

1840
02:04:52,603 --> 02:04:53,728
You ready, Mr. Conlon?
Aye.

1841
02:04:53,812 --> 02:04:55,188
I know the difference
between right and wrong.

1842
02:04:55,272 --> 02:04:56,481
I know.
The truth has to come out.

1843
02:04:56,565 --> 02:04:57,690
They may not want to hear it
in the court,

1844
02:04:57,775 --> 02:04:59,525
but there's people outside
who'll listen.

1845
02:04:59,610 --> 02:05:00,860
Just think about it, will you?

1846
02:05:00,944 --> 02:05:02,028
Just think about it.

1847
02:05:02,112 --> 02:05:03,154
All right.

1848
02:05:03,238 --> 02:05:04,781
Aye. Give us three of them.

1849
02:05:20,589 --> 02:05:21,839
Silence!

1850
02:05:25,260 --> 02:05:30,139
In the matter of Her Majesty vs.
Gerard Patrick Conlon,

1851
02:05:31,058 --> 02:05:33,518
the case is hereby dismissed.

1852
02:05:38,065 --> 02:05:40,400
My husband died in your
prison an innocent man!

1853
02:05:40,484 --> 02:05:42,860
I'm going out the front door.
I'll see you outside.

1854
02:05:42,945 --> 02:05:44,070
I'll see you outside.

1855
02:05:44,154 --> 02:05:45,822
This way. Let's go.
I'm going out the front door.

1856
02:05:46,198 --> 02:05:47,365
What about Guiseppe Conlon?

1857
02:05:47,574 --> 02:05:49,909
Your Honor, he was an innocent man!

1858
02:05:52,704 --> 02:05:54,914
Mr. Conlon, that's not a good idea.
Use the back...

1859
02:05:54,998 --> 02:05:56,249
For security reasons.

1860
02:05:56,333 --> 02:05:57,959
I'm a free man, and I'm
going out the front door.

1861
02:05:58,669 --> 02:05:59,710
Get back.

1862
02:05:59,795 --> 02:06:03,673
In the matter of
Her Majesty vs. Paul Hill,

1863
02:06:03,757 --> 02:06:06,551
the case is hereby dismissed.

1864
02:06:13,934 --> 02:06:17,478
Leave me alone!
I'm going out the front door with Gerry!

1865
02:06:20,607 --> 02:06:25,027
In the matter of Her Majesty vs.
Patrick Armstrong,

1866
02:06:25,279 --> 02:06:27,947
the case is hereby dismissed.

1867
02:06:29,992 --> 02:06:33,995
In the matter of Her Majesty vs.
Carole Richardson,

1868
02:06:34,079 --> 02:06:36,998
the case is hereby dismissed.

1869
02:06:37,916 --> 02:06:39,375
I'm an innocent man!

1870
02:06:39,501 --> 02:06:43,629
I spent 15 years in prison
for something I didn't do!

1871
02:06:43,714 --> 02:06:45,548
I watched my father die

1872
02:06:45,632 --> 02:06:48,217
in a British prison
for something he didn't do!

1873
02:06:48,385 --> 02:06:51,220
And this government
still says he's guilty!

1874
02:06:51,305 --> 02:06:53,181
I want to tell them

1875
02:06:53,265 --> 02:06:56,309
that until my father
is proved innocent,

1876
02:06:56,393 --> 02:06:59,979
until all the people involved in
this case are proved innocent,

1877
02:07:00,063 --> 02:07:02,648
until the guilty ones
are brought to justice,

1878
02:07:03,108 --> 02:07:04,775
I will fight on

1879
02:07:05,194 --> 02:07:07,779
in the name of my father

1880
02:07:07,900 --> 02:07:09,779
and of the truth.